default_js_slang:
default_js_slang(_program: string) → {any}

When use this function as the entrance function in the parameter of "set_evaluator", the Programmable Repl will directly use the default js-slang interpreter to run your program in Programmable Repl editor. Do not directly call this function in your own code.
module_display:
module_display(content: any) → {any}

Redirects the display message into Programmable Repl Tab If you give a pair as the parameter, it will use the given pair to generate rich text and use rich text display mode to display the string in Programmable Repl Tab with undefined return value (see module description for more information). If you give other things as the parameter, it will simply display the toString value of the parameter in Programmable Repl Tab and returns the displayed string itself.
set_background_image:
set_background_image(img_url: string, background_color_alpha: number) → {void}

Set Programmable Repl editor background image with a customized image URL
set_evaluator:
set_evaluator(evalFunc: Function) → {undefined}

Setup the programmable REPL with given metacircular evaulator entrance function
set_font_size:
set_font_size(font_size_px: number) → {void}

Set Programmable Repl editor font size
